Terrible service. They ruined our night. We should had left as soon as we walked in. I went to Morelos tonight with another 5 friends because of their Tuesday Taco special. The waitress refused to honor the taco deal advertised on their website. We were told that the deal was over and we would have to pay the regular price. We let her know that her colleague confirmed the night’s special when we walked in. She replied by saying that the other waitress “was new to the restaurant and didn’t know well how it works.” She brought guacamole to the table eventhough we didn’t request. Finally, when the bill came, after spending almost $120, we were charged 4% extra because We were paying the check with one credit card. In other words, after 15 years living in NYC, this is the first time a restaurant passes to me THEIR credit card fee responsibility. When we left, we saw a poster attached to the  restaurant window. Indeed, Taco Tuesdays goes until midnight. We went back inside, told her what we read on the poster,  and complained. She told us she would tell her manager to change the information on poster. The Mexican citizen in our group who is visiting NYC was chocked by  the service and the terrible quality of the meal. In conclusion, this is a restaurant serving mediocre food and fooling the neighborhood with deals they cannot deliver. This is the first and last time I eat or bring people there.
